{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Ganji Bar''' is the lower valley region form the old flow of the rivers [[Satluj]] and river [[Beas River|Beas]] or river [[Hakra]] to river Ravi . District lying in this area is [[Bahawalnagar]]. "Bar" is the name given to areas in [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]] which were thick forests or barren lands before the advent of the new canal irrigation system.

The dominant culture of this region is [[Bari Culture]] and native language spoken is [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]], spoken with various dialects. After the introduction of canal system, many lands of this area were granted to people mostly belong to various districts of Eastern Punjab.
